To Create catkin_ws follow these commands:
-------------------------
Note: For every new project you need to create new packages in catkin_ws!

1) mkdir catkin_ws
2) cd catkin_ws/
3) mkdir src/
4) catkin_make
# this will create catkin_ws

5) cd devel/
6) source setup.bash
7) atom ~/.bashrc
#it will open the source code, at last line type: source ~/catkin_ws/devel/setup.bash
#and save the fiel
--------------------------

Creating ROS Package

1) cd catkin_ws/src/
2) catkin_create_pkg robot roscpp rospy std_msgs  
              ## here instead robot, you can use your own words

Now, open new terminal and type
1) cd catkin_ws/
2) cd catkin_make

---------------------------
To Run Python Programs:

1) cd catkin_ws/src/robot/
2) mkdir scripts
3) cd scripts/
4) touch your_pythonfilename.py
5) chmod +x your_pythonfilename.py
#you created puthon file

----------------------------
To access python file:
     atom your_pythonfilename.py
To run that python file:
    python3 your_pythonfilename.py
